{"name": "openvino-telemetry", "metadata": {"name": "openvino-telemetry", "version": "2024.5.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/openvinotoolkit/telemetry", "license": "OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "OpenVINO\u2122 Telemetry package for sending statistics with user's consent, used in combination with other OpenVINO\u2122 packages.", "upload_time": 1732031065}, "documentation": ["#  OpenVINO\u2122 Telemetry\r\n\r\nThe implementation of the Python 3 library to send the telemetry data from the OpenVINO\u2122 toolkit components.\r\n\r\nTo send the data to Google Analytics, use the following three variables: `category`, `action`, and `label`.\r\n\r\n- In the `category`, use only the name of the tool. Place all Model Optimizer (MO) topics in the 'mo' category, all Post-Training Optimization Tool (POT) topics in the 'pot' category. \r\n- In the `action`, send a metric or a function, such as accuracy, session, conversion, and others. For example, for MO use: version, framework, conversion_results.\r\n- In the `label`, send more detailed data for your action (function). For example, send a string with the version name for the version or a string with the framework name for the framework. You can send a string with a wrapped dictionary: \"{param: value, version: value, error: value}\".\r\n\r\n**NOTE:** If you want to track the connection between data (for example, on which operating systems error '123' occurred), send the data in one event and add it to the label together. Example: telemetry.send_event(\"mo\", \"error_info\", \"{os:ubuntu18, error:123}\"). If you send the data separately, you will not be able to identify the connection. Some data will be duplicated since the same metric/function will be sent in different events.\r\n\r\n**NOTE:** Sending of telemetry data requires user's consent during installation of OpenVINO\u2122 toolkit component. In case if control file does not exist on the system or it contains a \"no\" answer, no data will be transmitted. \r\n\r\n**TIP:**  To help automate the analytics, always send **all** the keys for a dictionary in the `label` variable. If a key is empty, send 'none' as its value. \r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "openvino_telemetry", "documentation": ["Copyright (C) 2018-2024 Intel Corporation", "SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "openvino_telemetry.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "openvino_telemetry.Telemetry", "xref": {"fqname": "openvino_telemetry.main.Telemetry", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "openvino_telemetry.opt_in_out", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python3", "Copyright (C) 2018-2024 Intel Corporation", "SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0"], "functions": [{"name": "openvino_telemetry.opt_in_out.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "openvino_telemetry.backend.backend_ga", "documentation": ["Copyright (C) 2018-2024 Intel Corporation", "SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0"], "functions": [{"name": "openvino_telemetry.backend.backend_ga.is_valid_cid", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cid", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "openvino_telemetry.backend.backend_ga.GABackend", "bases": ["TelemetryBackend"], "methods": [{"name": "openvino_telemetry.backend.backend_ga.GABackend.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tid", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"na